>An 8 watt light draws 2/3 amp (not 1/2) so the time to run the light 
>before the battery will not start the engine is 68*25/0.66 = 2575 min, or 
>just under 43 hours.

And anything you can run off of 12 volts directly such as a TV or a light 
or whatever I would. The inverter itself consumes some power - mine gets 
warm with a large load. Mine also runs a fan when it is on.

You can get a variety of 12 volt appliances from the RV catalogs.


